summary: The document is a memorandum from the Deputy Director of Security (Investigations and Operational Support) to the Chief of the Technical Services Division, concerning the return and destruction of alias documentation issued to James P. O'Connell in April 1962. The documentation, which includes a California Driver's License, Social Security Card, Reserve Officer's Association Membership Card, and an Auto Insurance ID Card, was deemed no longer necessary. The memo acknowledges the swift processing of this matter.
key_findings: The document details the issuance and return of alias documentation for James P. O'Connell.
It illustrates the procedural steps involved in managing sensitive documentation within the CIA, particularly the destruction of obsolete documents.
The memo emphasizes the critical nature of operational security and the confidential management of alias identities.
